name: Cooper
description: How sweet is that face? This is Cooper. He's a 5 month male Terrier pup. He is super sweet, likes to be with his people and comes out of his shell with just a little love! His adoption fee is $360. He is neutered/vaccinated/micro-chipped/vet checked and comes with 30 days free pet insurance. Come down and meet him! 2201 S. 19th Ave, Phoenix. We are open daily from 11 am to 6 pm.

name: Boi West
color: White with Tan, Yellow or Fawn
description:
I'm a good Boi!  I'm great with other dogs and kids!  Boi is a 2 year old pitty miX.  He has the cutest markings ever!  He walks good on the lead and is a quick learner.  He can jump fences which could have been due to lack or exercise or boredom, or being left outside alone for long periods of time. He may need to be supervised while outside or coyote rollers may be needed.  Regardless he is a great boy, and with a little training, he will stop jumping fences.  If you have no breed restrictions and feel you can provide Boi with the great home he needs please call 520-800-4633 asap.  HE IS URGENT!  A MEET AND GREET WITH ALL FAMILY MEMBERS AND DOGS IS REQUIRED AT THE SHELTER.MEET >>>BOI !! A#4040485>> He/She is courtesy posted for Maricopa County Animal Care & Control.

Approximately >> 6years old and looking for a furever home!

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for Maricopa County Animal Care & Control and is at the WEST VALLEY facility (2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix). Different adoption fees/policy apply. 

Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours and detailed location information. You may wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify that it is still available and/or has not been moved to a different adoption center for more visibility to potential adopters.

name: Riggs
description: If interested in this dog, please go to www.dalmatianrescueco.org and submit an application for adoption. Under Adoptions, please read our adoption policy.  We must have an application before we can begin the adoption process and each dog does have foster contact listed.

name: Princess
description:
Animal Profile: Princess is a big sweatheart -- only 16 months old and likely an Anatolian Shepherd mix. She weighs 78 lbs and is not done growing! She loves people and has just arrived to our rescue. We will update her profile with more information soon.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $475, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue. 

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated in her foster home.
